HEADWORD: maternity ward
<hw>ma*ter"ni*ty ward`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The section
of a hospital devoted to assisting women during childbirth and caring
for them and their newborn infants until they are released to go
home.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

